Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @baking potato{2} into wedges roughly the thickness of your index finger (no need to peel!). Put them on a lined #baking tray{} and drizzle over a little @olive oil{a little}. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch}. Toss to coat then spread out evenly in a single layer and pop on the top shelf of your oven. Cook until crispy, around ~{30-35%minutes}, turning halfway through cooking.

Peel and grate the @ginger{1}(peeled and grated) and zest the @lime{1}(zested). Pop the ginger and lime zest into a #mixing bowl{} with half the @peanut butter{1/2}, the @mayonnaise{1%spoonful} and stir. Add the @pork sausage meat{225%g} and the @panko breadcrumbs{9.9%g} and mix everything together with your hands. Form into 1-2cm thick burgers - they will get fatter as they cook (one per person).

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Peel the @carrot{2}(peeled and coarsely grated) and remove the ends then coarsely grate into another mixing bowl. Roughly chop the @coriander{5}(roughly chopped, stalks and all) and add it to the carrot. Halve the @baby gem lettuce{1}(halved lengthways) then slice widthways thinly. Add to the bowl. Roughly chop the @salted peanuts{15}(roughly chopped) and mix into the salad. In a #small bowl{}, combine the lime juice, the remaining @peanut butter{1/2}, the @white wine vinegar{12%ml} and @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Set aside.

Heat a splash of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Once the oil is hot, add the burgers. Fry until brown and cooked through, ~{6-7%minutes} on each side.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when they are no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, halve the @brioche bun{2}(halved). When the wedges have 5 mins remaining, pop the brioche on another baking tray on the bottom shelf of your oven to warm through and toast slightly.

Dress the slaw with the peanutty dressing and toss together gently. Place a small amount of slaw on the base of each bun, then top with a burger, a spoonful of mayo and the brioche bun lid. Serve with the potato wedges and remaining slaw on the side. Enjoy!